name: Push Ups
description: Traditional pushups are beneficial for building upper body strength. They work the triceps, pectoral muscles, and shoulders.

name: Dumbell Row
description: Dumbbell rows put special emphasis on your back muscles, including the latissimus dorsi, posterior deltoids, teres major, trapezius, and rhomboids.

name: Squats
description: Squats burn calories and might help you lose weight. They also lower your chances of injuring your knees and ankles.

name: Abdominal Crunches
description: Like situps, crunches help you build muscle. But unlike situps, they work only the abdominal muscles.

name: Lunges
description: Lunges increase muscle mass to build up strength and tone your body, especially your core, butt, and legs.

name: Burpees
description: With burpees, the focus is on a full-body calisthenics workout that aims to build muscle strength and endurance in both your lower and upper body.
